## üîß OAuth Provider Credentials (To Be Configured)

### Google OAuth
**How to get**: See OAUTH_SETUP_GUIDE.md ‚Üí Section 1
```env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com"
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your-google-client-secret"
```

**Redirect URI to configure in Google Console:**
- Development: `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google`
- Production: `https://your-domain.com/api/auth/callback/google`

---

### Facebook OAuth
**How to get**: See OAUTH_SETUP_GUIDE.md ‚Üí Section 2
```env
FACEBOOK_CLIENT_ID="your-facebook-app-id"
FACEBOOK_CLIENT_SECRET="your-facebook-app-secret"
```

**Redirect URI to configure in Facebook App:**
- Development: `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/facebook`
- Production: `https://your-domain.com/api/auth/callback/facebook`

---

### Apple OAuth (Optional - Requires Apple Developer Account)
**How to get**: See OAUTH_SETUP_GUIDE.md ‚Üí Section 3
```env
APPLE_CLIENT_ID="com.azamaza.web.service"
APPLE_CLIENT_SECRET="eyJhbGciOiJFUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..." # Generated JWT
```

**Redirect URI to configure in Apple Developer:**
- Production only: `https://your-domain.com/api/auth/callback/apple`
- Apple requires HTTPS, localhost won't work

---

## üìù Setup Priority

1. **Required for basic authentication**: 
   - ‚úÖ AUTH_SECRET (Already set)
   - ‚úÖ NEXTAUTH_URL (Set to localhost for dev)

2. **Optional OAuth providers** (Add as needed):
   - Google OAuth (Easiest to set up)
   - Facebook OAuth (Medium difficulty)
   - Apple OAuth (Requires paid developer account)

3. **For production deployment**:
   - Update NEXTAUTH_URL to production domain
   - Generate new AUTH_SECRET for production
   - Add production redirect URIs to OAuth providers

---

## üöÄ Quick Start

To test authentication without OAuth providers:

1. The app already supports email/password authentication via the backend API
2. OAuth buttons will be visible but non-functional until credentials are added
3. To add OAuth:
   - Follow OAUTH_SETUP_GUIDE.md for your chosen provider(s)
   - Add credentials to .env
   - Restart development server

---

## üîí Security Notes

- **Never commit .env to version control**
- Keep AUTH_SECRET secure (treat like a password)
- Regenerate AUTH_SECRET for production
- Use different OAuth credentials for dev/prod
- Store production secrets in secure environment (Vercel, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)

